<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="479" type="mainText">
Remarks: This very successful tramp species has a nearly pantropical distribution nowadays. Even though it likely originates from the Ethiopian Region (Bolton 1982), it is very probable that it has been transferred artificially to Socotra also. Colonies are small and cryptic and these ants are thus rarely collected. Like all its congeners, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Cardiocondyla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emeryi">Cardiocondyla emeryi</taxonomicName>
is characterised by the relatively wide postpetiole and total absence of erect dorsal body hairs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
